<br>
<br>
<br>
The circle of life... Or what is should be. A child is born, brought screaming into this world by a women and a man. A child grows into an adult if lucky and grows from experience. A child is something I never had the pleasure of being. No... Not me. Created? Formed? Manufactured perhaps... but not born… <br>
<br>
<br>
“Do you think it will work?” the young Tier’Dal asked, gazing at his master in wonder.<br>
<br>
“Hush Dron. I need to concentrate now, we shall see is it will work or not” <br>
<br>
“Yes, of course forgive me.”<br>
<br>
The old wizard laid the dead body on a table before him with extreme care; the price the necromancer asked for the corpse was too great to pay twice. The blue skin of the young male was covered in tattoos, his skin flawless; the bastard necromancer had not lied when he said he would find a prime specimen. He was young, he had to be, this body must last.<br>
<br>
“Bring me the rune, its time to begin” the old wizard croaked, stress and excitement breaking into his normally calm voice. <br>
<br>
“Yes Master, here you are.”<br>
<br>
The old wizard placed the rune on the body, the spot marked by the head of a black phoenix. He stepped back, nerves making his hands quiver in fear of the sin he was about to commit. Breaking the laws of nature, the laws of Tunare herself. Making life not of a women and a man but of death, fire and magic. <br>
<br>
“It begins.” He whispered, more to himself then to be heard.<br>
<br>
He pushed up this sleeves and began the incantation, the arcane words flawless as he spoke. He had been working for this moment for years, perfecting the spell, finding body after body to experiment with. All before this had failed horribly, the spell was to strong, the corpses could not handle the fiery spirit, burning into ashes on the table. He was sure this time would work; he would have his creation, his demon pet. The thoughts raced through his mind, he would be the creator of this new perfect race, created to serve Fennin and the fires of Ro. <br>
<br>
As the old man worked the rune began to glow bright, the tattoos on the body faded from a coal black to a crimson red, clashing with the blue skin on the body. Fire licked the ends of the table, threatening to char the precious body and end the spell in failure just like the rest. The old man opened his eyes with the last of the words, watching the fire lick the body.<br>
<br>
“No!” he cried out “Not again.”<br>
<br>
With a speed unnatural to his age he pulled the ice spell to his mind, in a mad attempt to douse the fires. He was too late, the room itself had begun to glow, smoke filled his eyes blinding him. <br>
<br>
“Dron!” he called out to the young boy “Get out of the room, close the door behind you!”<br>
<br>
It was too late, in his concentration the fires had consumed the right half of the room. Blocking the exit trapping both him and the boy. The boy was franticly casting every ice spell he could call to mind at the taunting fire to no avail. The searing heat was unnatural, it consumed the furniture and shrugged off the cold magic like an annoying insect. <br>
<br>
“I fear this is the last time I will fail at this. I don’t think ill be trying again” <br>
<br>
The old man watched the dancing red and yellow though the thick smoke as it grew ever closer. He and his apprentice would die here,  slowly, consumed by the very fires he called to this realm.<br>
<br>
                                       *                *                 * <br>
“Ugh.. “ The young man groaned, searing pain in his back and chest.<br>
<br>
He sat up slowly, opening his crimson eyes for the first time, a young male in his early 20’s. He shook his pounding head, trying to clear his foggy vision. Sliding off the table he crumpled to a heap on the ground, his legs would not support him. <br>
<br>
“ Where..” He whispered, his voice smooth and unwavering.<br>
<br>
His eyes shot open at the sound, this was not his voice, this was not his body and this was definitely not his home. He struggled to his feet, forcing his eyes to scan the blackened room, nothing but stone and ash. It was then fear and bewilderment set in, he was alone naked and in pain. Fighting to walk he stumbled to a wall, using it as support to stand. A sick crunch rang out form under his foot as he crushed the skull of a boy, the bone so frail and weak from the fire it crushed like an egg shell. <br>
<br>
“Where am I “ he thought, unwilling to hear the strange voice again. “How did I get here?!”<br>
<br>
He struggled to clear his mind, How did he get here? What was going on? Who was he? He crouched down in the ashes in the dark corner of the room the sick realization finally setting in. He did not remember why his voice sounded so different, he did not remember how he got here, and he did not remember anything before this moment. Panic set in as he fought to make sense of things. <br>
<br>
“Think, think fool. What was the last thing you remember? Where were you? What were you doing?!” His mind raced.<br>
<br>
There was no answer to his questions, his mind was blank. He was new to this realm, not born but created. The knowledge of how to speak, how to walk and think perhaps remnants of the body he was forced into, perhaps the mind of his soul, perhaps fed to him though the destructive fire that breathed life into his chest. More questions he could not answer, there were only questions, never answers.<br>
<br>
<br>
