<br>
Hours passed into days, days into weeks and weeks into months. After the fire there was not much left of the lab tucked deep away in the Rathe mountains. The food storage and dining area were damaged but otherwise intact, the only room that remained untouched was the old wizard’s bed chambers. For months he pawed over books and notes, bits and pieces of arcane script, and journals, fruitlessly. The old wizard had covered his tracks well, to well, the only scrap of useful information that could be found was a scribbled list of names and spell components. Flame agates, corpses, parchment, ink all useless, save for one item. At the bottom of the list was the most resent purchase, “corpse: Tier’Dal , Draehan Aramil.” <br>
<br>
            *                           *                            *      <br>
  <br>
“Hello!” The booming voice of the massive warrior was loud even though the thick wooden door.<br>
<br>
“Hay! any one home?” Groganthanos boomed once more before his massive foot turned the door in on itself. <br>
<br>
The huge man grinned as he looked in the remains of what once was an entrance hall. He had to duck fit under the door frame, the Ogre stood a good 8 feet tall well over the capacity the home was built to handle.<br>
<br>
“If you’re here you may as well come out now! Hide and you’ll regret it!” He stood his full height, his bald head grazing the ceiling of the room, allowing his voice to echo off the walls.<br>
<br>
Draehan could hear the voice from the bed chamber like a trumpet. He worked quickly, unsure of what to expect. The precious notes were tucked away in a hidden wall storage before he made his way quietly out into the dinning area. The massive room was empty save for the long table, the door to the entrance hall at the opposite side of the room. A voice, something his ears had never heard before rang out once more.<br>
<br>
“This is your last chance old man; don’t make me come find you!”<br>
<br>
Draehan stood silent by the doorframe, a small flame danced on his fingers. He readied to defend himself if needed, though any thing he could have thrown at the warrior would have only proven to anger him. He stepped into the main hall boldly, knowing very well there was no where to hide in the remains of the home.<br>
<br>
“There yo-.. Hey, you’re not Malories. Get your master out here, he has some explaining to do!” the Ogre growled fiercely.<br>
<br>
Draehan stood quiet for only a moment, the name now burned into his mind “Malories”.. One more piece to the puzzle fell into place. <br>
<br>
“He’s not here” Draehan’s voice was soft, his vocal cords still not working fully for he had not used them yet.<br>
<br>
“Well when will he be back? I have a score to settle and an arena to run damn it, if he doesn’t show his wrinkled face out here in 15 minuets im making him sorry he ever placed any bets.” <br>
<br>
It was then the images sunk in to the Ogres mind, the normally lavish room was almost empty, the walls black with carbon. What was left of the tapestries hung in taters, the rugs half burnt. He gaped a moment before turning a sharp glare at the robed Tier’Dal.<br>
<br>
“Bandits eh? .. Well this here house owes me a debt and I don’t care whose liven here... you had better pay.”<br>
<br>
“Bandits?.. “ Draehan's whisper of a voice was filled with confusion. “What bandits?”<br>
<br>
“Well if your not here to rob the place when what happened here? Explain boy. “Groganthanos spoke quickly, growing impatient.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know... I’m afraid I can’t tell you anything.” <br>
<br>
The large warrior eyed the young man once more, his patience growing thin.<br>
<br>
“Fine, if you won’t talk then I’ll just take my payment. I could use some fodder for the arena and you’ll fit the bill just fine me thinks.” <br>
<br>
He said nothing more, he didn’t need to. With one swing of his massive club the still weak Tier’Dal was laid out on the floor. It took the Ogre only moments to drag him from the hall and toss him limply in the back of his wagon. Draehan could not hear the words that would have driven fear into any casters mind.<br>
<br>
“The people love a good fight, well see how you do with out your finger wigglen in the area boy. “<br>
