                 *                      *                      * <br>
<br>
Entering the old halls the memories of fear and confuses flashed in his mind as if they were only days past.<br>
<br>
“This place is a wreck...” He spoke to himself, his voice an eerie echo on the bare walls.<br>
<br>
The room was just as he left it, half burnt and charred. Blackened furniture and tapestries lined the stone walls. The dining hall and study were much worse; the fire had died as it reached the main hall. As always the only place to rest was the main bed chambers, untouched by the fire. Draehan ran his hand along the wall, feeling for the place he tucked the notes four years past.<br>
<br>
“I know it was... “ his voice was cut short as a small click opened the hidden panel. “here.”<br>
<br>
He pulled out the notes but did not look them over; he knew what they said already. Placing them on the desk his glance fell to the door and the room past. The keep had once been the old wizards home and Draehan would now make it his. Much of the wood had been destroyed but simple things such as that were replaceable. The money from the arena would be enough to rebuild what was lost.<br>
<br>
                 *                                             *                                  * <br>
<br>
Draehan sat in the main hall at his desk finishing off the last of his work. A wooden plaque that would soon hang over the door of the entrance... “Fireforge keep” <br>
